﻿## Description
The PATCH /api/auth/role endpoint allows **any authenticated user** to update any user's role (including granting themselves dmin privileges). It only applies uthMiddleware (JWT authentication) but is **missing isAdmin or any role-based authorization check**.

## Location
- **File**:  ackend/src/routes/auth.routes.js (line 80)
- outer.patch("/role", authMiddleware, authController.updateRole);

## Vulnerable Code
`
// auth.routes.js:80 — no isAdmin middleware!
router.patch("/role", authMiddleware, authController.updateRole);
`

`
// auth.controller.js:155-165 — accepts userId and role from body
export const updateRole = catchAsync(async (req, res) => {
  const { userId, role } = req.body;
  if (!['user', 'admin'].includes(role)) {
    return sendResponse(res, 400, false, 'Role must be "user" or "admin".', null);
  }
  const user = await authService.getMe(userId);
  if (!user) return sendResponse(res, 404, false, 'User not found.', null);
  user.role = role;
  await user.save();
  sendResponse(res, 200, true, 'Role updated successfully', { id: user._id, role: user.role });
});
`

## Impact
**Complete privilege escalation.** Any registered user can:
1. Call PATCH /api/auth/role with { "userId": "<their-id>", "role": "admin" }
2. Gain full admin access
3. Access all admin endpoints (e.g., DELETE /api/admin/users/:id, etc.)

## Expected Fix
Add an isAdmin middleware before uthController.updateRole:
`
router.patch("/role", authMiddleware, isAdmin, authController.updateRole);
`

## Steps to Reproduce
1. Register a new user account and get the JWT token
2. Send PATCH /api/auth/role with body { "userId": "<your-user-id>", "role": "admin" }
3. Observe the response confirms role changed to admin
